	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post102457"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Candarie</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">the Healer</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Mar 2002<br>
	Location: Thurgadin, Velious, Norrath<br>
	Posts: 92</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b>On the Druid/Shaman CH</b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I feel the need to start a bigger fire on this issue; since I just saw it in action for the first time and noticed something that wasn't made clear to me as a tester and likely wasn't clear to anyone else.<br />
<br />
I have remained cool and supportive of most of these changes, and up until now, I even supported the idea of the 75% CH, at least as I understood how it worked.<br />
<br />
This "75% CH" ... Does not heal the target to 75% of their life.  It *gives* them 75% of their life back.<br />
<br />
AKA - If your target is not at less than 25% of their life, it *is* a Complete Heal.<br />
<br />
Now, some druid/shaman is going to flame me and talk about some uber ass tank with 7000 hp and how there is a total HP cap and all this other nonsense that is being waved at us as a cushion for just how serious this spell is.<br />
<br />
Thats a LOAD.   Here is my example.  This goes out to all of you that always want to know how this affects the less than uber, the everyday, the average cleric.<br />
<br />
I was doing a duo xp camp with Hurthem, arguably one of the stronger warriors on the server that is not so uber he scoffs at items from ToV.  He has a partial suit of Skyshrine quest armor.  His guild can do Tormax and ST, but he doesn't really have loot from there (btw Sleeper intact on test).  Hurthem also has a crazy amount of AA, something like 120+.  He's a great guy too. My opinion is that most clerics will not see a warrior that is much better overall than Hurthem.<br />
<br />
Hurthem also packs a druid bot on a 2box.  He happily gives up the druid spot with him to group with me ... He didn't have to; he's just nice like that and we're friends.<br />
<br />
So anyway, he gets down to about 30 life, and I start to cast CH.  Hurthem's HP jumps to Full!  Suprised I look around and nope, no other clerics.  I ask him and yup, sho nuff, that was all 2box druid.<br />
<br />
Its just a game, but I had to log afterwords.  The thought of the 110 played days I blew in the last year made me cry.<br />
<br />
EDIT: <i>typos</i></font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
Venerable <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=357314" target="_blank">Candarie the Healer</a><br />
High Priestess of the <a href="http://pub137.ezboard.com/beqtestregistry" target="_blank">Test Server</a></font></p></p>
