	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">The answer should be that he got healed for 10500.  That is the new message on CH.<br />
<br />
And now we know why.<br />
<br />
On a side note, i have been exping and thinking abotu these issues the last couple days.<br />
<br />
I am not in an uber guild, or even a second tier guild.  We have a close knit and small guild.  I don't do pickup groups.<br />
<br />
It is not unusual for us to group with whatever classes feel like grouping.  Yesterday, I went to the Hole with a 52 Monk, 53 war, 52 druid, 59 druid, 58 bard (who joined later) and myself, 60 cleric.  <br />
<br />
My mana was good throughout the hunt, although both druids had mana issues.  No one died, although we did succor on two occasions due to massive overpulls (priior to the bard showing up for mez duty).  I was pulling due to level, and I usually do alright there, but there are occasions when aggro is flaky.<br />
<br />
I used DA twice.  Once when we got three golems and the bard had trouble mezzing due to resists.  The first time I used DA, I got aggro after I CH'd the warrior to start off the three golem pull.  In about 5 seconds, those three golems pounded me down to two bubbles of life and I hit DA.  If there had been three druids instead of 2 druids and a cleric, I think the CHing druid would have been killed.  Then they would have had to CR somehow with no cleric.<br />
<br />
If druids are casting CH, they are going to die from heal aggro (not every time, but it will happen).  If there is no cleric in the group, the group is going to have trouble.<br />
<br />
If druids are casting CH, they are not going to be very effective at succoring.<br />
<br />
My guild tells me that we tend to go do fun stuff when the clerics are online, and when they aren't, most folks are duoing or soloing or working on trade skills.<br />
<br />
I only know what happens when I am online, and when I am online, they will follow me anywhere.<br />
<br />
When my rogue says "lets go do XXXX", they want to know if the other cleric is goign to come.  <img src="../ubb/tongue.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
I think many clerics, myself included may be jumping the gun on the danger of some of this stuff.  I am very curious about players attitudes on Test right now.<br />
<br />
Do the test players think that they would rather group with a druid in chardok then a cleric?<br />
<br />
Do the test players around level 55 prefer a CHing druid or a CHing cleric in Seb or Velks or does it change in outdoor zones like ME or UP?<br />
<br />
Do the changes on Test help out guilds doing raids stuffs, and do they hinder clerics in exp groups, basically, and if so, what levels and where?<br />
<br />
Thanks<br />
<br />
Tarf Crackleberry<br />
High Priest <br />
Quellious Server</font></p>
	
