<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post102560"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Candarie</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">the Healer</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Mar 2002<br>
	Location: Thurgadin, Velious, Norrath<br>
	Posts: 92</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Do the test players think that they would rather group with a druid in chardok then a cleric?<br />
<br />
Do the test players around level 55 prefer a CHing druid or a CHing cleric in Seb or Velks or does it change in outdoor zones like ME or UP?  <br />
<br />
Do the changes on Test help out guilds doing raids stuffs, and do they hinder clerics in exp groups, basically, and if so, what levels and where?<br />
<br />
---------------<br />
<br />
I would love to give you more specific answers; in my opinion, the answer is Yes to all of these questions, in every zone, at all levels 47+. <br />
<br />
I'm not going to try and map out the zones etc for 2 reasons.  <br />
<br />
First, every mention of zones by myself, teac, or Rich Waters has been met with flamage and the content being ignored /drowned by cries of "whoopdeedo, x zone doesn't count because of y or its your gear that lets you do z"<br />
<br />
Second, Test is a server like a small town.  While sure, there is some degree of class preference where appropriate, alot of it is drowned out because you are known for *who* you are.  I still get groups that need a healer or that don't, just because I'm around and there's room. <br />
<br />
--------------<br />
<br />
On the other topic, The heal did what its supposed to do at the moment ... Gave him 75% of his life back.  Since he aimed it to hit at 25% or more remaining, it was a full heal.  Since he wasn't raidbuffed (Raidbuffs are worth close to 2khp these days), and isn't a Luclin equipped uberguild maintank, closer to the average population, Hurthem didn't hit or was right at the 2900 cap for 75% of his life.  Which means he was cruising at a little under 4khp.  My math tells me that if you're at 4khp,and we get 2khp for raidbuffs, thats 6k of the high end 7kish that the best of the best have; most of us dont have that.  The less than 60s that will be affected by this, they don't have that.  Rough numbers here of course, flamesuit on.<br />
<br />
If you don't like my math, just take it at this: I seen it with my own two eyes, I'm not speculating, the way it is now, is overpowered.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
Venerable <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=357314" target="_blank">Candarie the Healer</a><br />
High Priestess of the <a href="http://pub137.ezboard.com/beqtestregistry" target="_blank">Test Server</a></font></p></p>
