<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="95%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor=""  width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post102578"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Xenu</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Cleric</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Mar 2000<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 96</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">"Healing someone to 75% would be stupid; I don't think the majority of people assumed it would work like that"<br />
<br />
Might be stupid in a group situation. On a raid situation, it would do well as addition to the cleric CH chain, making druids a viable addition to clerics without replacing them completely.<br />
<br />
If it was really capped at 75%, then it would still make druids more usefull on raids and lessen the need for huge numbers of clerics - while still not making clerics obsolete in regular groups.<br />
<br />
With 75% being a minor limitation rather then a real cap, we get this very real threath to sub-60 clerics who are not uberguilded.<br />
<br />
Personally i'm not all that worried. I'm a twink, just dinged 46. My main is in the primary uberguild of my server (the only guild in VT so far), and I have lots of friends in the servers only euro timezone uberguild. Both guilds have their tanks equipped well enough to notice a very real difference between Cleric CH and Druid CH. There will always be room for me. And actually I was planning to get my xp by duoing with a druid anyway, playing the role of guess what? Yep, battle cleric. <br />
<br />
Fun for me and those like me. Yay for us. But what about the other 99% of the game population?<br />
<br />
In the name of fairness for the normal everyday cleric, I claim this:<br />
<br />
Either make 75% a real cap for the druid/shaman CH, and give clerics some nice stuff to compensate.<br />
Or, let the druids and shaman have this real CH that heal you from 25% health to full - and give the clerics insane upgrades on the edge of wreaking game balance completely.<br />
<br />
The current "limitations" to druid CH are just fluff to pretend that it's not a real CH. It is. That is, it's a real CH for all purpouses - perhaps with ONE exception: highend raids, the one thing that the spell was supposed to fix.<br />
<br />
Make 75% a hardcap, just like 50% normally is for bind wounds.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
	<p align="right"><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><a href="report.php?s=1fb9fd3cdaf8ccd9b8b20af37e416c85&postid=102578">Report this post to a moderator</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=1fb9fd3cdaf8ccd9b8b20af37e416c85&action=getip&postid=102578">Logged</a></font></p>
	</td>
</tr>
