<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor=""  width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post102586"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>ajax34i</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Vicar</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Jan 2001<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 101</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I always assumed that's how it was going to work.  What it means is basically they can CH a tank just as well as clerics, for MORE mana.  The more hps the tank has, the earlier the druid has to start his/her CH, and the more often they have to cast it.    <br />
<br />
If the tank has 7k HPs and the damage doesn't come in too fast, they can basically start the first ICH at 1.5 bubbles, take the tank to 70% health, then ICH again for full health, total cost 800 mana, end result tank full.<br />
<br />
The only time this doesn't work is if the tank gets hit a lot.   There's a range in there where as damage on the tank increases, only a real CH will do, and then as the damage taken increases further, even the clerics will need to switch to a CH chain to cope.<br />
<br />
But yeah, they're basically replacement for clerics right now.  All they need to do is manage their mana right.  That was the point of the change.<br />
<br />
There was talk of aggro on some other threads...  Remember when Verant said spells generate aggro proportionate to INTENT?  How a wizzie resisted ice comet that hits for 20 has the same aggro as one that hits for full?  Our CH hits for 10k.  The druid CH hits for 3k max?  Way less aggro.  And if the tank knows what he or she is doing, even CH aggro doesn't matter.  I've sat down after CH's countless times.<br />
<br />
It's a fully functional, perfectly reasonable, CH ability.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><i>Last edited by ajax34i on 08-24-2002 at 07:16 PM</i></font></p>
